WEBVTT

00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:09.802
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.928 --> 00:00:14.015
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.932 --> 00:00:16.767
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.896
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:26.027 --> 00:00:26.986
Guts...

00:00:27.153 --> 00:00:28.904
...are you thinking of...

00:00:36.412 --> 00:00:40.207
Are you going to leave the Hawks?

00:01:00.686 --> 00:01:02.855
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:03.064 --> 00:01:04.815
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:05.024 --> 00:01:08.569
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:08.778 --> 00:01:10.946
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:11.072 --> 00:01:13.032
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:13.157 --> 00:01:15.201
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:16.077 --> 00:01:17.036
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:17.286 --> 00:01:20.706
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:20.915 --> 00:01:24.335
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:25.086 --> 00:01:25.711
<i>I...</i>

00:01:26.087 --> 00:01:26.837
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:26.962 --> 00:01:28.964
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:29.173 --> 00:01:30.049
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:30.216 --> 00:01:30.966
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:31.175 --> 00:01:32.843
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:32.968 --> 00:01:33.969
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:34.970
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:35.096 --> 00:01:36.931
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:37.181 --> 00:01:38.099
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:38.224 --> 00:01:39.058
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:39.225 --> 00:01:40.726
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:40.976 --> 00:01:42.061
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:42.228 --> 00:01:43.187
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:43.312 --> 00:01:43.979
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:44.105 --> 00:01:45.606
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:54.615
The Decisive Battle

00:02:23.394 --> 00:02:24.186
Message!

00:02:24.270 --> 00:02:24.895
Message!

00:02:25.312 --> 00:02:26.313
I have a report!

00:02:26.438 --> 00:02:27.940
Our army has
endured immense damage!

00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:30.442
Only this headquarters remains intact!

00:02:30.818 --> 00:02:32.528
What a fine state of affairs!

00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:37.074
We, the White Tiger Knights, have one
of the strongest armies in all of Midland...

00:02:37.199 --> 00:02:39.201
...and we have been beaten so easily!

00:02:39.702 --> 00:02:42.913
This Castle of
Doldrey is quite impregnable!

00:02:43.289 --> 00:02:44.331
I have a report!

00:02:44.707 --> 00:02:45.916
Now what?

00:02:47.293 --> 00:02:49.962
We've confirmed a thousand cavalrymen
marching from the main gate of the fort!

00:02:50.421 --> 00:02:52.798
They are charging our headquarters!

00:02:54.091 --> 00:02:55.092
What?

00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:57.219
The strongest of all Chuder's armies...

00:02:57.344 --> 00:02:59.096
The Purple Rhino Knights?

00:03:30.878 --> 00:03:32.504
This Hundred Year War...

00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:36.342
...was triggered by the Chuder
Empire's invasion on Midland's territory.

00:03:37.343 --> 00:03:39.345
The Castle of Doldrey once belonged...

00:03:39.470 --> 00:03:41.972
...to our kingdom as an
integral part of our defenses.

00:03:42.514 --> 00:03:44.391
Ironically, this fort has
become a staging point...

00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:48.270
...for attacks by the Chuder
army ever since they captured it.

00:03:48.896 --> 00:03:52.399
However, civil war may break forth
at any moment in the Chuder Empire...

00:03:52.608 --> 00:03:54.485
...in regards to the
matter of imperial succession.

00:03:54.777 --> 00:03:57.655
Most likely, the Empire cannot...

00:03:58.030 --> 00:04:02.117
...afford to spare all of its
great military forces for this war.

00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:05.037
Indeed, this is a rare opportunity for us!

00:04:05.246 --> 00:04:07.414
We can't miss this opportunity
to achieve the conquest of Doldrey!

00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:09.667
No, to recapture of our fief!

00:04:10.042 --> 00:04:12.002
Very well, what shall we do about it?

00:04:12.169 --> 00:04:14.672
The principal garrison stationed
there is the Purple Rhino Knights.

00:04:14.797 --> 00:04:17.258
They are led by the fierce general
Boscogn, and there are no stronger knights...

00:04:17.383 --> 00:04:18.759
...anywhere in the Empire!

00:04:19.093 --> 00:04:21.011
Even our most powerful asset...

00:04:21.136 --> 00:04:23.514
...the White Tiger Knights, suffered
great losses when engaging them.

00:04:25.015 --> 00:04:26.642
An all out attack...

00:04:26.767 --> 00:04:28.352
...that might be our final option.

00:04:28.894 --> 00:04:30.020
That is very risky!

00:04:30.771 --> 00:04:32.356
Consider the overall campaign...

00:04:32.398 --> 00:04:34.984
...we've already lost forty
percent of our total fighting strength.

00:04:35.401 --> 00:04:36.485
There is no guarantee...

00:04:36.652 --> 00:04:38.988
...that we will conquer Doldrey
even if we deploy all of our assets.

00:04:39.113 --> 00:04:40.531
If the war is prolonged...

00:04:40.656 --> 00:04:44.410
We'd likely be caught between their
main army and the occupation forces!

00:04:44.743 --> 00:04:47.121
If we are rash, we'll risk the
annihilation of our entire armed forces.

00:04:47.371 --> 00:04:50.916
I predict that this campaign
will eventually lead us to victory.

00:04:51.125 --> 00:04:53.377
Therefore, such a dangerous
gamble is not worth the risk.

00:04:53.544 --> 00:04:58.132
But, our final objective in this
war is to take control of Doldrey!

00:04:58.424 --> 00:05:01.552
Occupying Doldrey is absolutely
essential if we want to recapture our fief!

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:04.430
However, which unit will be
considered for the role of the vanguard?

00:05:04.555 --> 00:05:07.057
Remember this, we
lost the White Tiger Knights.

00:05:07.266 --> 00:05:08.309
Well...

00:05:10.436 --> 00:05:12.563
What would you say, Sir Griffith?

00:05:12.813 --> 00:05:18.569
Even your invincible band, the Hawks,
wouldn't be able to handle this, right?

00:05:19.695 --> 00:05:21.405
We could, if given the order.

00:05:21.697 --> 00:05:24.199
I understand, the
matter goes over your head...

00:05:24.450 --> 00:05:25.200
Hey...

00:05:30.331 --> 00:05:32.916
If Your Majesty gives me an order...

00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:33.917
Nonsense!

00:05:34.043 --> 00:05:35.294
Do you think you can really do it?

00:05:35.461 --> 00:05:37.046
Your Lordship understands
nothing about the difficulties!

00:05:37.463 --> 00:05:40.215
He has gotten a rather swelled head...

00:05:40.466 --> 00:05:43.594
...on account of his
lucky victories in the past.

00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:44.553
I agree.

00:05:44.678 --> 00:05:47.556
During the past one hundred years,
that castle has never been damaged...

00:05:47.723 --> 00:05:50.809
...even though it has frequently stood
against our desperate attempts to capture it.

00:05:50.934 --> 00:05:52.561
However, you still
say you could conquer it?

00:05:53.479 --> 00:05:54.855
My Lord, Griffith...

00:05:57.358 --> 00:05:58.609
Can you truly do this?

00:06:00.986 --> 00:06:02.613
He is just reckless, Your Majesty!

00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:06.325
The Doldrey conquest requires us
to employ an enormous armed force!

00:06:06.492 --> 00:06:10.245
If we fail at this time, it will cause a
great deal of permanent damage to us...

00:06:11.622 --> 00:06:13.957
I do not need to engage
them with a large army.

00:06:14.833 --> 00:06:18.087
The Band of the Hawk
alone will cope with this matter.

00:06:18.504 --> 00:06:19.254
What!

00:06:19.380 --> 00:06:20.130
It's impossible!

00:06:20.255 --> 00:06:21.256
Who do you think you are?

00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:24.009
Don't be ridiculous!

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:26.136
A mere force of five thousand men...

00:06:26.261 --> 00:06:29.848
...can deal with the enemy's
occupation force, thirty thousand men strong?

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:33.519
Don't get carried away
with your playing around, boy!

00:06:33.977 --> 00:06:38.273
I bet you wish your cunning
little schemes could be used forever!

00:06:38.524 --> 00:06:39.358
General...

00:06:40.776 --> 00:06:43.404
There is no use raising your eyebrows.

00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:44.279
What?

00:06:44.738 --> 00:06:47.741
Sooner or later, we will
have to venture into total war.

00:06:47.866 --> 00:06:50.411
Apparently, we are left with
no other options in this matter.

00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:55.290
Since it's apparent that a defeat or two
won't harm our army's morale, we can...

00:06:55.499 --> 00:06:57.918
...then try out their maneuver
before calling for an all out attack.

00:06:58.377 --> 00:07:02.297
And considering the Band
of the Hawk's past achievements...

00:07:02.506 --> 00:07:05.050
...it's unfair to say that
they will have no chance at all.

00:07:05.259 --> 00:07:07.052
Do not underestimate Doldrey!

00:07:08.804 --> 00:07:09.680
Damn...

00:07:10.889 --> 00:07:13.308
Majesty, you had best pass judgement.

00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:27.823
I command that the Hawks commit
themselves to the conquest of Doldrey!

00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:34.079
His Majesty has certainly aged.

00:07:34.204 --> 00:07:37.207
How could he rely upon a
newcomer, a boy like him?

00:07:37.583 --> 00:07:40.669
The army of Midland
has lost all of its dignity.

00:07:45.591 --> 00:07:46.675
Well...

00:07:46.925 --> 00:07:50.220
I can imagine how he feels, but
there's nothing I can do about it...

00:07:50.846 --> 00:07:53.098
You have quite a high
opinion of that man, don't you?

00:07:53.849 --> 00:07:58.979
I wonder if the White Hawk will rise
to the occasion, as you expect he will.

00:07:59.855 --> 00:08:03.358
Well, I told them the truth either way.

00:08:04.359 --> 00:08:07.112
Even if he loses
the battle after all this...

00:08:07.321 --> 00:08:08.739
...in Midland today...

00:08:08.864 --> 00:08:11.200
...there is no other man capable
of executing the conquest of Doldrey.

00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:12.868
Certainly.

00:08:28.717 --> 00:08:31.345
It may be strange
for a man to say this...

00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:34.640
...but he looks as if he
just stepped out of a painting.

00:08:35.015 --> 00:08:36.808
A commander beyond all others...

00:08:38.185 --> 00:08:43.315
Perhaps, we have
fought by a hero such as that...

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:46.318
...one who only
emerges once in a hundred years.

00:08:47.819 --> 00:08:49.196
Doldrey, huh?

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:51.573
Whatever, I don't care about that.

00:08:52.407 --> 00:08:55.827
You'll win any war or dice
game, if that's what is meant to be!

00:08:58.080 --> 00:08:58.956
There!

00:09:00.082 --> 00:09:01.708
There you go!

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:03.043
Get outta here!

00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:04.836
Winning ten times in a row?

00:09:04.962 --> 00:09:07.464
The Commander won everything again.

00:09:08.674 --> 00:09:10.801
You really have the
devil's own luck, boss!

00:09:10.926 --> 00:09:11.468
All right!

00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:13.720
I'll never give up until
I get my money back!

00:09:14.555 --> 00:09:15.472
What's wrong?

00:09:16.598 --> 00:09:19.059
Is there something worrying you?

00:09:19.184 --> 00:09:20.602
N-No...

00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:22.854
Don't worry.

00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:26.608
We've been through
this kind of thing before.

00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:30.487
If a self-respecting man
like him offered to fight...

00:09:30.737 --> 00:09:32.447
The odds must be in his favor.

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:38.245
I hope he keeps his head...

00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:44.001
Do you remember what
I told you some time ago?

00:09:44.876 --> 00:09:49.756
When the Hawks became involved in a
territorial dispute in a certain region...

00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:52.009
Griffith...

00:09:52.259 --> 00:09:53.260
I mean...

00:09:54.011 --> 00:09:55.762
That nobleman you mentioned...

00:09:56.138 --> 00:09:58.724
Shit, the Commander won again?

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.101
Give me a break!

00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:04.896
That nobleman was promoted
to governor in a certain empire...

00:10:05.731 --> 00:10:09.151
His bribe money spoke the loudest
when the position was awarded.

00:10:11.153 --> 00:10:12.654
Hey, don't tell me he...

00:10:14.031 --> 00:10:18.660
The governor of the Empire of
Chuder's Northlands, Governor Gennon.

00:10:20.037 --> 00:10:22.372
That's the title he currently holds.

00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:34.301
Sir Adon, we are glad to see you safe.

00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:37.804
I, Lord Adon, known far and wide...

00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:40.307
...as an invulnerable and highly
resourceful general, would never die so easily!

00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:42.934
Anyway, that boy...

00:10:43.060 --> 00:10:47.689
If I meet him in the battlefield again,
I definitely won't let him get away!

00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:50.400
For shame, Adon!

00:10:56.907 --> 00:10:59.076
Your Grace, General Boscogn!

00:10:59.201 --> 00:11:01.203
To settle a personal grudge...

00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:06.333
You deployed all of those mercenaries,
and all you achieved was total defeat!

00:11:06.458 --> 00:11:09.961
Even worse than that, your
brother Samson's life was lost!

00:11:10.212 --> 00:11:13.173
You've got a lot of nerve, coming
back here alone after causing...

00:11:13.215 --> 00:11:14.800
...such disgrace!

00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:16.343
No, uh...

00:11:17.594 --> 00:11:19.429
I-It is not true, Your Grace...

00:11:19.471 --> 00:11:20.430
Truthfully...

00:11:21.807 --> 00:11:23.600
This is outrageous!

00:11:37.364 --> 00:11:41.993
From now on, I thoroughly divest
you of the right to command in this war.

00:11:42.577 --> 00:11:45.997
You should appreciate the fact that I'm
not going to throw you into the dungeons!

00:11:51.753 --> 00:11:56.216
The opponent was reportedly
only one soldier, just as was rumored...

00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:58.135
That cannot be...

00:12:03.598 --> 00:12:06.393
You were strict as usual.

00:12:06.518 --> 00:12:08.270
I could even hear
your shouting from up here.

00:12:09.271 --> 00:12:11.898
Please excuse my manner,
which seems unpleasant to your ear.

00:12:12.274 --> 00:12:13.650
All right then.

00:12:14.151 --> 00:12:18.280
By the way, according to my spies...

00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:23.493
...the second wave for the
conquest of Doldrey has been chosen.

00:12:26.747 --> 00:12:29.040
You know them well by now...

00:12:29.291 --> 00:12:30.667
...the Band of the Hawk.

00:12:32.794 --> 00:12:34.546
You look happy.

00:12:35.297 --> 00:12:37.299
No, I do not mean to...

00:12:37.549 --> 00:12:40.260
But they seem to be
much more difficult to deal with...

00:12:40.302 --> 00:12:43.430
...than the other opponents, who
rely only on numbers and reputation.

00:12:46.516 --> 00:12:51.646
Anyhow, I need to have a word
with you before you set off for battle.

00:12:53.190 --> 00:12:57.444
The leader of the Hawks is
known as the White Hawk Griffith.

00:12:58.695 --> 00:13:00.822
You must not kill that one.

00:13:01.823 --> 00:13:05.327
Keep him alive and bring him to me.

00:13:05.702 --> 00:13:06.578
However...

00:13:07.078 --> 00:13:10.040
Keep it in mind, this
is your governor's order.

00:13:38.235 --> 00:13:40.195
How are your wounds, still hurt?

00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:42.572
I'm fine now.

00:13:43.073 --> 00:13:45.116
Thanks to the medicine you gave me.

00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:49.496
Even so, the more I see that
fortress, the less confident I feel.

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:54.251
The castle walls are doubly built,
twice as high and thick as any other castle.

00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:56.253
The far side is
protected by a sheer cliff...

00:13:56.378 --> 00:13:59.256
And, the Purple Rhinos
are stationed there as well.

00:13:59.589 --> 00:14:02.509
No big deal, it's just
like any castle, only bigger.

00:14:02.717 --> 00:14:04.886
We just do it the way we always have.

00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:06.596
I hope so, anyway.

00:14:12.227 --> 00:14:14.396
Either way, I'm surprised.

00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:16.898
He burned all the boats.

00:14:20.610 --> 00:14:23.280
What on earth is the
White Hawk thinking?

00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:27.659
I wonder if his tactic is to take a
position with his back to the river?

00:14:28.285 --> 00:14:29.411
All right, then.

00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.997
They can hold out temporarily
just because of their numbers.

00:14:32.163 --> 00:14:35.542
Our army will march
squarely into their ranks.

00:14:36.376 --> 00:14:37.419
However...

00:14:38.169 --> 00:14:42.549
Does the governor happen
to have some relation to him?

00:14:44.885 --> 00:14:47.804
Well, it's a waste of time for me
to worry about such absurdities!

00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:53.393
My duty is only to tear my
opponents apart until the end!

00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:00.317
The White Hawk...

00:15:01.401 --> 00:15:04.571
I have never imagined that
I would see him alive again.

00:15:05.530 --> 00:15:07.198
I'll definitely have him.

00:15:08.450 --> 00:15:10.702
Look at all of this dust!

00:15:11.703 --> 00:15:13.413
It's a part of my plan.

00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:17.083
Are you all right?

00:15:23.715 --> 00:15:24.424
Good.

00:15:24.716 --> 00:15:25.967
It's about time to move.

00:15:32.974 --> 00:15:36.227
I hope he keeps his head...

00:15:36.978 --> 00:15:38.480
It'll never happen.

00:15:38.939 --> 00:15:41.483
He's the last man to lose his calm...

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:49.824
This is the last time...

00:15:53.078 --> 00:15:55.205
...I wield my sword under this flag...

00:15:55.872 --> 00:15:57.499
First formation, advance!

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:06.132
But I'm not going to leave
any loose ends behind me...

00:16:07.008 --> 00:16:10.470
I'm going to take full responsibility
as the leader of the Hawk's Raiders!

00:16:11.888 --> 00:16:12.889
Draw your swords!

00:16:16.643 --> 00:16:18.019
First formation, charge!

00:16:20.897 --> 00:16:22.023
The first formation contains...

00:16:22.273 --> 00:16:25.610
...two thousand men directly under the
control of Griffith and his top companies!

00:16:25.902 --> 00:16:27.028
What nonsense...

00:16:27.278 --> 00:16:30.657
Dividing his army into two formations,
when he only has five thousand men?

00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:34.744
What is he trying to prove by
relying on his cunning alone?

00:16:35.412 --> 00:16:37.288
Very well, I'll accept your challenge!

00:16:37.539 --> 00:16:39.040
All units, charge!

00:16:39.165 --> 00:16:41.292
Grind the enemy's
first formation into dust!

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:52.262
Are these the Hawk's Raiders
we've heard so many reports about?

00:16:52.387 --> 00:16:53.179
Interesting!

00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:11.239
One of the enemy's companies
is bursting through our front line!

00:17:11.656 --> 00:17:14.909
They aim to get at our army's
leaders by breaking through head-on...

00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.037
Is this the scheme of the White Hawk?

00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:30.425
Follow the Commander!

00:17:34.929 --> 00:17:35.805
This can't be!

00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:39.267
Nothing has ever checked
the Purple Rhino's assault before...

00:17:39.517 --> 00:17:41.561
We can't keep pressing forward
now, we might even be repelled!

00:17:41.770 --> 00:17:42.562
General!

00:17:43.271 --> 00:17:44.314
That's him.

00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:50.320
Reportedly, he wiped out one
hundred mercenaries all by himself...

00:17:50.528 --> 00:17:52.572
It seems that report
was not altogether false.

00:17:52.697 --> 00:17:55.408
Well, the White Hawk
possesses good personnel.

00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:57.160
Remain steadfast!

00:17:57.327 --> 00:17:59.537
They're just trying
to disrupt our discipline!

00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:02.832
Fall back into
formation, then counterattack!

00:18:04.793 --> 00:18:08.838
The Hawks fight well
against the Purple Rhino Knights...

00:18:10.465 --> 00:18:12.592
But they will soon realize their limits.

00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:18.723
Boscogn, it seems you see this
battle as an opportunity to kill Griffith...

00:18:21.184 --> 00:18:22.477
Someone, attend to me!

00:18:22.852 --> 00:18:23.812
Yes, sir!

00:18:24.729 --> 00:18:27.857
Have my personal
guard prepare to take the field.

00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:31.486
I will command
directly from the battlefield!

00:18:32.612 --> 00:18:34.989
However, what
about defending the castle?

00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:36.449
Pay no mind!

00:18:37.075 --> 00:18:39.744
Under these
circumstances, the Hawks cannot...

00:18:39.953 --> 00:18:42.247
...get any closer to the castle walls.

00:18:42.705 --> 00:18:43.373
Yes, sir!

00:18:44.249 --> 00:18:46.626
My precious hawk
is coming back to me...

00:18:46.876 --> 00:18:49.587
I'm not going to let
him be killed for nothing.

00:18:55.009 --> 00:18:57.011
It's time, Captain!

00:18:57.512 --> 00:18:58.638
All companies, retreat!

00:18:58.763 --> 00:18:59.764
Regroup at the base camp!

00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:02.976
Come on men, get moving!

00:19:12.152 --> 00:19:13.903
The enemy is retreating!

00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:15.280
Start the pursuit!

00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:16.531
Strange!

00:19:17.407 --> 00:19:19.033
They must have
foreseen the consequences...

00:19:19.159 --> 00:19:21.161
...since they chose
this particular strategy.

00:19:21.411 --> 00:19:25.665
Did the invincible White
Hawk really plot this scheme?

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:27.375
I'm not going to contradict you...

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:30.545
...but maybe you think too
highly of those men, General?

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.673
Never mind that, just give us
the command to pursue them!

00:19:34.424 --> 00:19:36.676
If we let them get away...

00:19:36.801 --> 00:19:39.262
...the soldiers will miss their
chance to win the spoils of war...

00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.014
...and they will
complain to their superiors.

00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:43.308
What are you doing, Boscogn?

00:19:45.310 --> 00:19:46.644
Governor-general!

00:19:47.145 --> 00:19:48.813
The enemy is retreating.

00:19:49.063 --> 00:19:51.316
Will you miss a chance for
victory just to observe them?

00:19:51.941 --> 00:19:53.193
No, but...

00:19:54.694 --> 00:19:56.070
I order everyone!

00:19:56.696 --> 00:20:00.074
Do not kill the
enemy's leader, Count Griffith!

00:20:00.825 --> 00:20:02.452
Capture him alive!

00:20:04.829 --> 00:20:06.456
I promise that anyone who succeeds...

00:20:06.664 --> 00:20:09.083
...in capturing him will be
immediately promoted two ranks!

00:20:09.209 --> 00:20:11.085
I will reward you
with whatever you want!

00:20:12.170 --> 00:20:13.087
Governor!

00:20:13.463 --> 00:20:15.798
You should not promise such things.

00:20:15.965 --> 00:20:16.841
I care not!

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.219
But it affects military discipline!

00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:19.969
Boscogn!

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:24.224
From now on, I am
taking command directly!

00:20:24.849 --> 00:20:27.852
The Purple Rhino Knights are
to immediately pursue the enemy!

00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:33.316
Notify the entire army of my orders!

00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:34.484
Make sure it is enforced!

00:20:35.944 --> 00:20:36.861
General...

00:20:37.362 --> 00:20:38.738
It has nothing to do with me.

00:20:38.988 --> 00:20:41.491
All units, move to
pursue the enemy!

00:20:46.079 --> 00:20:49.499
We're completely outnumbered,
and I'm bringing up the rear all by myself.

00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:55.004
But after everything, they are
taking the bait, just as Griffith planned.

00:20:57.257 --> 00:21:01.511
Yeah, everything was executed so
it would play perfectly into your hand...

00:21:01.761 --> 00:21:02.845
As always...

00:21:05.515 --> 00:21:07.016
What a thrilling view!

00:21:08.393 --> 00:21:11.396
We're not going to deal
with all of that, are we?

00:21:13.648 --> 00:21:15.024
Formations, regroup!

00:21:18.736 --> 00:21:20.363
We are reaching a crucial moment.

00:21:20.989 --> 00:21:22.282
Our backs are to the river!

00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:23.533
There's no way to escape!

00:21:30.623 --> 00:21:31.791
Stake your lives on this fight!

00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:34.669
To survive, we have no choice
but to stake our lives on this fight!

00:21:35.420 --> 00:21:36.796
If we are able survive...

00:21:36.921 --> 00:21:38.172
...we are as good as victorious!

00:22:03.072 --> 00:22:05.199
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.408 --> 00:22:08.911
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:10.079 --> 00:22:12.957
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:13.041 --> 00:22:15.918
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.587 --> 00:22:19.172
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.213 --> 00:22:20.423
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.548 --> 00:22:23.593
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:27.722
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.930 --> 00:22:31.100
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.434 --> 00:22:34.729
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:35.104 --> 00:22:38.107
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.733 --> 00:22:41.819
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:45.490
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:10.390 --> 00:23:15.770
If one only tastes victory in order
to survive, a defeat will never be allowed.

00:23:16.270 --> 00:23:22.610
Tortured and saddened, such a
man never has his back to the victory.

00:23:23.653 --> 00:23:26.030
To capture a dream, he will
always be required to shed blood.

00:23:26.656 --> 00:23:31.035
Again, this is the fate that
will befall a youthful heart.

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
The Conqueror

